subsection.def:
Authority
                    (醫管局) means the Hospital Authority
                established under section 3(1);

Chairman
                    (主席) means the Chairman of the Authority
                appointed under section 3(3)(a);

committee
                    (委員會) means a committee established under
                    section 13;

paragraph.content:
in accordance with the provisions of this Ordinance and the relevant agreements
                referred to in section 5(a) entered into, manage and control public
                hospitals;

subparagraph.content:
to use hospital beds, staff, equipment and other resources efficiently to
                    provide hospital services of the highest possible standard within the resources
                    obtainable;

paragraph.content:
employ such persons as it thinks fit to carry out hospital services or any
                other matter relating to the performance of its functions or the exercise of its
                powers;

engage the services of such technical and professional advisers as it thinks
                fit to advise the Authority on any matter relating to the performance of its
                functions or the exercise of its powers;

undertake and execute any lawful trust which has as an object the furtherance
                of any function which the Authority is required or is permitted by this Ordinance to
                perform or any other similar object;

establish and maintain a system for providing a proper consideration of
                complaints from users of hospital services, or of members of the public, in relation
                to hospital services;

paragraph.continued:
to the extent that the provisions of any such specified document are
                    inconsistent with the provisions of that agreement or this Ordinance;
                    and

subsection.def:
Hospital Chief Executive (醫院行政總監), in relation to a public hospital,
                    means the person appointed by the Authority to be the Hospital Chief Executive
                    for the public hospital;

section.text:
the Chief Executive may declare his office as a member of the Authority to be
                vacant, and shall notify the fact in such manner as the Chief Executive thinks fit;
                and upon such declaration the office shall become vacant.

subparagraph.content:
is a member of the Authority referred to in section
                        3(3)(d);
                        and

paragraph.content:
monitor public opinion and review the pattern of any complaints about
                    hospital services in the region and suggest improvements to the provision of
                    hospital services in the region;

1 representative, not being a public officer or member of the staff of
                        the Authority, of the Regional Advisory Committee, if any, established for
                        the region in which the teaching hospital is situated;

such number of members as is agreed between the Authority and the governing
                    body of the prescribed hospital and nominated by the governing body;
                    and

subparagraph.content:
to optimize the utilization of hospital beds, staff and equipment to
                        ensure the public hospital provides hospital services of the highest
                        possible standard within the resources obtainable;
